HEADWORD: Pederero
<hw>Ped`e*re"ro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>pedrero</ets>, fr. OSp. <ets>pedra</ets>, Sp. <ets>piedra</ets>, a
stone, L. <ets>petra</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>pe`tra</grk>. So named because
it was at first charged with stones.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A
term formerly applied to a short piece of chambered ordnance.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>paterero</asp> and
<asp>peterero</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

